                  <handDesc>
                     <p>The writing is in a very praticed hand, which does not resemble closely that of the known Egyptian tablets. On the whole, the writing is more like that of the best Pompeian tablets than of the Dacian, though in time it is apparently close to the Dacian examples. (Sanders)</p>
